The paper deals with self-adjusting data structures, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for heaps, which falls under the category of algorithm design and analysis (cs.DM). The paper uses lower bounds and optimality theory, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses instance-specific upper bounds and applications, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
